text.tspan: Daily confirmed COVID-19 deaths vs. confirmed cases per million, Mar 19,
Shown is the rolling 7-day average. The number of confirmed cases is lower than the number of total cases. The main reason
for this is limited testing. Comparisons across countries are affected by differences in testing policies and reporting methods.
The grey lines show the ratio between daily confirmed deaths and confirmed cases.
